=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from 5,7-dibromo-4-chloroazaindazole/pyrrolopyrimidine core; perform a regioselective Suzuki coupling with 2,6-dichlorophenylboronic acid to give the monoarylated bromochloro intermediate, 7-bromo-5-(2,6-dichlorophenyl)-4-chloro-heteroaryl scaffold. | Step 2: N-alkylate the ring NH of this scaffold with enantiopure N-Boc-(S)-3-(bromomethyl)piperidine (or the corresponding mesylate) to install the N-CH2-[C@@H](piperidine) side chain, giving the Boc-protected piperidine intermediate. | Step 3: Displace the remaining activated 4-chloro group by SNAr with 2,4-difluorobenzylamine to form the 4-(2,4-difluorobenzylamino) intermediate while retaining the aryl and bromo substituents. | Step 4: Remove the Boc group from the piperidine nitrogen (e.g., TFA or HCl/dioxane) to furnish Fc1ccc(CNc2ncc3c(Br)c(-c4c(Cl)cccc4Cl)n(C[C@@H]4CCCNC4)c3n2)cc1F.

